    "recap_headline": "Brown University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PROVIDENCE, R.I. \u2013\nFour Brown pitchers combined to twirl a one-hitter on Tuesday afternoon in a 4-1 win over Quinnipiac at Attanasio Family Field at Murray Stadium.\nIan Keusch\n,\nMatt Wilmarth\n,\nBrenden Kline\nand\nChristian Keel\nheld the Bobcats hitless over the final eight innings as the Bears offense took the lead with three runs in the seventh.\nSix different Brown players combined for six hits, with freshman\nMatt Luigs\nand senior\nDJ Dillehay\neach collecting two RBIs. Junior\nAndrew Hanlon\nreached base three times and scored a run.\nKeusch went the first 3.1 innings and allowed one run on one hit. Willmarth tossed 1.2 scoreless innings, Kline used a big double play to toss a scoreless sixth inning, and Keel earned the win by tossing the final three inning and also compiled the only three strikeouts for the Bears' pitching staff in the game.\nThe Bobcats took a 1-0 lead in the first inning with an RBI single sandwiched around three walks. Hanlon tagged a runner out at the plate on a wild pitch that bounced off the backstop and right back towards the box to help Brown escape the inning.\nAlex Benevento\nled off the bottom of the fourth by reaching third base after an error on the right fielder, but a strikeout and double play kept Brown off the board.\nThe Bears evened the score in the fifth when\nJack Edmunds\nled off with a single and later scored on a sac fly by Luigs.\nThe Bears took the lead with three runs on three hits in the seventh. With runners on second and third with nobody out, Luigs lined one off the pitcher for an RBI single to give Brown the lead. Three batters later with two outs, Dillehay laced one through the left side to score Luigs and\nLogan Meusy\nwith two key insurance runs to spot the Bears a 4-1 lead.\nIN DJ WE TRUST!!\nDillehay gives Brown some cushion with a BIG two-out, two-run single to push it to 4-1!\nWatch on ESPN+\npic.twitter.com/Ys2byPjnwm\n\u2014 Brown Baseball (@BrownU_Baseball)\nMarch 10, 2026\nThe Bears will return to action this Friday-Sunday, March 13-15 with a three-game series at Seton Hall.\nBROWN UNIVERSITY SPORTS FOUNDATION\nThe Brown University Sports Foundation (BUSF) is the backbone of our athletics program, playing a crucial role in enhancing the student-athlete experience.\u00a0This\u00a0is possible through philanthropic support from our alumni, parents, fans, and friends.\u00a0Your\u00a0gift through the Sports Foundation can immediately impact today's Brown Bears, helping them excel in the classroom, in competition, and, most importantly, in the community. Please click\nhere\nto learn more about how\u00a0you\u00a0can support the Bears.\nFOLLOW US ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Brown Athletics, please follow\n@BrownU_Bears\non X and\n@BrownU_Bears\non Instagram. Like\nBrownUBears\non Facebook and subscribe to the\nBrownAthletics\nYouTube channel."
